    <title>Loss Functions Module</title>
    <briefdescription>
<para>Loss function implementations for model training. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<sect1 id="group__lossfx__module_1lossfx_overview">
<title>Overview</title>
<para>The Loss Functions module provides various loss function implementations for training machine learning models in physics applications.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__lossfx__module_1lossfx_functions">
<title>Available Loss Functions</title>
<para>The module includes loss functions suitable for:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Classification tasks (cross-entropy, focal loss)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Regression tasks (MSE, MAE)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Custom physics-informed losses</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classlossfx" kindref="compound">lossfx</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
